Technique: HEWN; WRITTEN WITH A REED PEN/REED WITH SPLIT NIB
Name: Limestone canopic jar
Description: This limestone canopic jar (see E.5898), originally in the Amherst collection, bears a text mentioning the name of the owner. The reading is uncertain, but it could be a woman called Setkhairbint. The version of the text indicates that this person lived during the 26th Dynasty.
